      "vein-content-1": {
        "type": "vein-content-1",
        "blocks": {
          "6d4e7894-094d-4b3f-bdf5-e53c2741edf5": {
            "type": "html",
            "settings": {
              "code": "<h3 class=\"h3 bottom-title\">Ultrasound Guided</h3>\n                <h1 class=\"text-main\">Sclerotherapy</h1><p>Ultrasound Guided sclerotherapy is useful to treat larger branch veins that are not visible to the naked eye. Ultrasound Guided Sclerotherapy done at re*be® uses a soapy foam material called sodium tetradecyl sulfate or polidocanol to close off the diseased vein. This substance is injected into the smaller veins using a needle. </p><p>The high resolution ultrasound machine we use at re*be® allows us to see veins that are not visible from the surface of the skin. This technique is most commonly used after an endogenous laser ablation procedure to treat and control branch vein disease. In many cases ultrasound guided sclerotherapy is medically necessary and may be covered by your Insurance. </p>",
              "width": "50%",
              "align": "auto"
            }
          }
        },
        "block_order": [
          "6d4e7894-094d-4b3f-bdf5-e53c2741edf5"
        ],
        "settings": {
